import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='y', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['y'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['y'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['y'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['y'].median():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of y values?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['x'] = pd.to_datetime(data['x'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['x'])]
    sns.scatterplot(x='x', y='y', data=data)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title('What is the relationship between x and y values?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['x'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='date', y='diff', data=data, ax=ax)
    ax.axhline(y=data['diff'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label=f"Mean: {data['diff'].mean():.2f}")
    ax.legend(loc='upper left')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title('What is the average difference between x and y values?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
